Demonstration of confidence sets in 1D

N = 20
x = seq( 0, 0.25, length.out = 200 )
mu_ModelA = function( x ){ sin( 8 * pi * x ) * exp( -3 * x ) }
noise_ModelA = BernsteinSumNoise
sigma_ModelA = function(x){ 3*( ( 1 - x - 0.4 )^2 + 1 ) / 6 }
dat_true = mu_ModelA(x)

M = FunctionalDataSample( N = n,
                          x = x,
                          mu =mu_ModelA,
                          noise = BernsteinSumNoise,
                          sigma = sigma_ModelA,
                          sd_ObsNoise =0)
SCB = SCB_dense(M)
est_mean <- apply(M, 1:2, mean)
source("../functions/plot_cs.R") 
#debug(plot_cs)
plot_cs(SCB, levels = c(-0.1, 0.2,0.8), x = x, y = x, mu_true =  dat_true, together = F)

Demonstration of confidence sets in 2D

N = 100
x = seq( 0, 1, length.out = 50 )
mu_ModelB = function( x ){  outer( x, x, "*" ) }
noise_ModelB = GaussDensitySum2DNoise
sigma_ModelB= function( x ){
  outer( x, x, FUN = function( s, t ) ( s + 1 ) / ( t^2 + 1 ) )
}
dat_true = mu_ModelB(x)

M = FunctionalDataSample( N = N,
                          x = x,
                          mu =mu_ModelB,
                          noise = noise_ModelB,
                          sigma = sigma_ModelB,
                          sd_ObsNoise = 0 )
SCB = SCB_dense(M)
est_mean <- apply(M, 1:2, mean)
source("../functions/plot_cs.R") 
#debug(plot_cs)
plot_cs(SCB, levels = c(0.2,0.3,0.5,0.7), x = x, y = x, mu_true =  dat_true, together = T)

ggsave("./figures/dense_2dshowcase.png")

Simluation coverage plotting

Model A

#Model A
#### Graphical parameters
level = 0.95
clab  = 1.5
caxis = 1.5
cmain = 2
#### Loading the data
#### Plot Sample paths of Signal plus noise model
set.seed(1)
# Model A sample paths
x = seq(0,1, length.out=200)
y = FunctionalDataSample( N=15, x=x, mu=mu_ModelA, noise=noise_ModelA, sigma=sigma_ModelA, sd_ObsNoise=0 )
df_plot_sample = as.tibble(cbind(x,y))%>% 
  pivot_longer(V2:V16, names_to = "line", values_to = "y") 
## Warning: `as.tibble()` was deprecated in tibble 2.0.0.
## Please use `as_tibble()` instead.
## The signature and semantics have changed, see `?as_tibble`.
## This warning is displayed once every 8 hours.
## Call `lifecycle::last_lifecycle_warnings()` to see where this warning was generated.
## Warning: The `x` argument of `as_tibble.matrix()` must have unique column names if `.name_repair` is omitted as of tibble 2.0.0.
## Using compatibility `.name_repair`.
## This warning is displayed once every 8 hours.
## Call `lifecycle::last_lifecycle_warnings()` to see where this warning was generated.
sample_path_plotA = df_plot_sample %>% ggplot(aes(x = x, y = y, color = line, linetype = line)) + 
  geom_line() + theme_light()+ 
  theme(legend.position = "None",plot.title = element_text(hjust = 0.5,face = "bold")) +
  xlab("Coordinates")+ylab("")+ggtitle("Model A")

#### Plot sample paths of noise
# Noise Model A plot
x = seq( 0, 1, length.out = 200 )
y = noise_ModelA( N = 15, x = x )
df_plot_noise = as.tibble(cbind(x,y))%>% 
  pivot_longer(V2:V16, names_to = "line", values_to = "y")

noise_path_plotA = df_plot_noise %>% ggplot(aes(x = x, y = y, color = line, linetype = line)) + 
  geom_line() + theme_light()+ theme(legend.position = "None",plot.title = element_text(hjust = 0.5,face = "bold")) +
  xlab("Coordinates")+ylab("")+ggtitle("Model A noise")

# Clear Workspace
rm(x, y)

#### Plot Simulation Results
#par( mar = c( 5.1, 5.1, 2.1, 2.1 ) )
df_result_sim = result_frame_1d %>% 
  select(N, SCB, Upper1000, Upper100, Upper25, Upper10, Upper5)%>% 
  pivot_longer(!c(N), names_to = "Simulation", values_to = "coverage_rate") %>% 
  mutate(coverage_rate = coverage_rate*100,
         N = as_factor(N),
         Simulation = fct_reorder(Simulation, coverage_rate))

result_sim_plotA = df_result_sim %>% ggplot(aes(x = N, y = coverage_rate,group = Simulation,color = Simulation)) + 
  geom_line()+
  geom_point(aes(shape = Simulation)) +ylim(c(84,100)) +
  geom_hline(yintercept = 100*(level+c(-2,2)*sqrt(level*(1-level)/n_sim)), linetype = 'dashed')+
  # scale_colour_discrete(labels = c("SCB", TeX(" $10^3$ levels"), 
  #                                  TeX(" $10 ^2$ levels"), TeX("$25$ levels"),
  #                                  TeX("$10$ levels"), TeX("$5$ levels"))) +
  scale_shape_discrete(labels = c("SCB", TeX(" $10^3$ levels"),
                                   TeX(" $10 ^2$ levels"), TeX("$25$ levels"),
                                   TeX("$10$ levels"), TeX("$5$ levels")))  +
  theme_light() +
  theme(legend.position = c(0.75, 0.2),legend.key.size = unit(0.2, 'cm')) +
  ylab("Coverage rate") +
  scale_color_brewer(labels = c("SCB", TeX(" $10^3$ levels"), 
                                    TeX(" $10 ^2$ levels"), TeX("$25$ levels"),
                                    TeX("$10$ levels"), TeX("$5$ levels")),palette = "PuBu", direction = -1)
sample_path_plotA + noise_path_plotA + result_sim_plotA + plot_layout(widths = c(1, 1,1))

ggsave("./figures/dense_1dsim_results.png")

Model B

#Model B
set.seed(1)
# Model B sample paths plot
x = seq(0,1,length.out=50)
y = FunctionalDataSample( N=15, x=x, mu=mu_ModelB, noise=noise_ModelB, sigma=sigma_ModelB, sd_ObsNoise=0 )

mu = y[,,9]
rownames(mu) = x      
colnames(mu) = x
mu = suppressWarnings(reshape::melt(mu))
colnames(mu)=c("X","Y", "Sample")

sample_path_plotB = ggplot()+
  geom_raster(aes(x=X, y = Y, fill = Sample), data = mu)+
  labs(fill = "") +# Make legend title to be empty
  ggtitle("Model B")+
  scale_fill_distiller(palette = "Spectral", direction = -1)+
  xlab("")+ylab("")+
  theme_light() +
  scale_x_continuous(expand = c(0.01,0.01)) + scale_y_continuous(expand = c(0.01,0.01))+
        theme(plot.title = element_text(face = "bold", hjust = 0.5,), plot.margin = unit(c(0.5,0,0,0), "cm"),
              legend.position = c(0.86, 0.25),legend.key.size = unit(0.3, 'cm'))



#### Plot sample paths of noise

# Noise Model B plot
x = seq( 0, 1, length.out = 50 )
y = noise_ModelB( N = 10, x = x )
mu = y[,,9]
rownames(mu) = x      
colnames(mu) = x
mu = suppressWarnings(reshape::melt(mu))
colnames(mu)=c("X","Y", "Sample")

noise_path_plotB = ggplot()+
  geom_raster(aes(x=X, y = Y, fill = Sample), data = mu)+
  labs(fill = "") +# Make legend title to be empty
  ggtitle("Noise Model B")+
  scale_fill_distiller(palette = "Spectral", direction = -1)+
  xlab("")+ylab("")+
  theme_light() +
  scale_x_continuous(expand = c(0.01,0.01)) + scale_y_continuous(expand = c(0.01,0.01))+
        theme(plot.title = element_text(face = "bold", hjust = 0.5,), plot.margin = unit(c(0.5,0,0,0), "cm"),
              legend.position = c(0.86, 0.25),legend.key.size = unit(0.3, 'cm'))



#### Plot Simulation Results
#par( mar = c( 5.1, 5.1, 2.1, 2.1 ) )
df_result_sim = result_frame_2d %>%
  select(N, SCB, Upper1000, Upper100, Upper25, Upper10, Upper5, cope5, cope10, cope25)%>% 
  pivot_longer(!c(N), names_to = "Simulation", values_to = "coverage_rate") %>% 
  mutate(coverage_rate = coverage_rate*100,
         N = as_factor(N),
         Simulation = fct_relevel(Simulation, levels = c("SCB", "Upper1000",
                                                         "Upper100", "Upper25",
                                                         "Upper10", "Upper5", 
                                                         "cope5",
                                                         "cope10", "cope25")))
## Warning: Outer names are only allowed for unnamed scalar atomic inputs
mypal <- colorRampPalette(rev(brewer.pal(6, "PuBu")))
mypal2 <- colorRampPalette(rev(brewer.pal(6, "YlOrRd")))
result_sim_plotB = df_result_sim %>% ggplot(aes(x = N, y = coverage_rate,group = Simulation,color = Simulation)) + 
  geom_line()+
  geom_point(aes(shape = Simulation)) +
  scale_shape_manual(values = c(rep(1,6), rep(2, 4)),
                     labels = c("SCB", TeX(" $10^3$ levels"),
                                TeX(" $10 ^2$ levels"), TeX("$25$ levels"),
                                TeX("$10$ levels"), TeX("$5$ levels"),
                                 "5 levels bonf", "10 levels bonf",
                                "25 levels bonf")) +
  scale_colour_manual(values = c(mypal(6), mypal2(4)),
                      labels = c("SCB", TeX(" $10^3$ levels"),
                                TeX(" $10 ^2$ levels"), TeX("$25$ levels"),
                                TeX("$10$ levels"), TeX("$5$ levels"),
                                "5 levels bonf", "10 levels bonf",
                                "25 levels bonf")) +
  ylim(c(69,100)) +
  geom_hline(yintercept = 100*(level+c(-2,2)*sqrt(level*(1-level)/n_sim)), linetype = 'dashed')+
  theme_light() +
  theme(legend.position = c(0.70, 0.25),legend.key.size = unit(0.01, 'mm')) +
  ylab("Coverage rate")


(sample_path_plotB + noise_path_plotB + result_sim_plotB) + plot_annotation(theme = theme(plot.margin = margin(10)))

ggsave("./figures/dense_2dsim_results.png")
